<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE: that is the chapter's point made by the build. Every failure path is handled
    the way the prose argues for — the body exception propagates while the close exception is collected
    as suppressed (never masked); the recoverable failure is a checked exception translated with its
    cause chained; the one broad catch is the justified boundary handler that logs and maps, so the
    REC_CATCH_EXCEPTION detector stays quiet because a checked exception genuinely reaches it. The
    filter is kept (empty) so a future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a home with a reason, rather
    than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
